value.value: An approach that improves the quality of life of patients and their families facing the problems associated with life-threatening illness, through the prevention and relief of suffering by means of early identification and impeccable assessment and treatment of pain and other problems, physical, psychosocial, and spiritualâ€™.
A service delivery system that provides palliative care/medicine when life expectancy is 6 months or less and when curative or life-prolonging therapy is no longer indicated.

definition.value: Treatment with an agent that can alter brain chemistry leading to mood and/or behaviorial changes.
Any surgical procedure conducted on the camera-type eye.

value.value: Care for patients with a progressive life-limiting disease with a prognosis of months or less.

definition.value: The production of heat in a body part by high-frequency electrical currents to stimulate circulation, relieve pain, cauterization, or destroy tissue.
A therapy using microwaves to focus on and heat up tissue with high water content, such as muscle.

A deep heating modality that uses high-frequency acoustic vibrations within body tissues for the treatment of certain medical conditions, such as the alleviation of pain, muscle spasms, and joint contractures.
Quantification of cell characteristics, including morphological or physiological parameter of one or more cells in order to determine the health of the patient and/or detect disease.

value.value: A form of deep heat therapy can induce vasodilatation, elevation of pain threshold, reduction in muscle spasm, acceleration of cellular metabolism, increased soft tissue extensibility, increase blood flow, decrease joint pain and stiffness, reduce inflammation, faster resolution of edema, and accelerate wound healing.
Any medical procedure used to sustain the life of a patient in critical condition.

definition.value: A measurement of the shape, structure, form, and size of cells from a patient to determine if there is disease and/or infection.
All manners of treatment to relieve illness and injury of a particular body site or system.
A clinical recommendation to avoid preventable diseases by vaccination or otherwise lowering risk for certain diseases.

Avoidance of an illness or infection that can be spread from person to person, animal to person, animal to animal or person to animal by taking precautionary measures, such as good hygiene practices or vaccines.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding or preventing Dehydration.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding or preventing Hypertension.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding or preventing Obesity.

label.value: inflammation of the skin prevention recommendation

definition.value: A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding or preventing Inflammatory abnormality of the skin.
Recommendation by a clinician to avoid exercise or physical activity.
avoidance of physical activity therapeutic recommendation
A recommendation by a clinician or therapist to avoid any impact activities to prevent medical issues or help the physical wellbeing of a patient.
A recommendation by a clinician or therapist to avoid isometric exercises to prevent medical issues or help the physical wellbeing of a patient.
A clinical recommendation to avoid or refrain from certain environmental exposures in order to maintain health or ameliorate symptoms.
A clinical recommendation to avoid or refrain from unnecessary radiation exposure.
A clinical recommendation to avoid or refrain from unnecessary sulight exposure.
A clinical recommendation to avoid the process of taking in of nutrients, especially by eating or drinking, considered in relation to the bodyâ€™s dietary needs.
Use of a substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

value.value: Medical treatment by means of drugs.

definition.value: Use of a drug to treat or prevent bacterial infections.
Use of a substance that inhibits or prevents the proliferation of neoplasms.

value.value: Sustained exercise that places an increased oxygen demand on the cardiovascular system and promotes an increased efficiency of the body's use of oxygen.
A medical recommendation of sustained exercise that places an increased oxygen demand on the cardiovascular system and promotes an increased efficiency of the body's use of oxygen.
The administration of oxygen to an individual, usually to aid in respiration.

Inhalation of oxygen aimed at restoring toward normal any pathophysiologic alterations of gas exchange in the cardiopulmonary system, as by the use of a respirator, nasal catheter, tent, chamber, or mask. (From Dorland, 27th ed & Stedman, 25th ed)

definition.value: A procedure designed to help you breathe easier when your lungs have been damaged by disease. The goal of the surgery is to remove the area of the lung most affected by disease, allowing the remaining lung to function more efficiently, and improve your breathing ability and quality of life.

value.value: Transference of a tissue or organ within an individual, between individuals of the same species, or between individuals of different species.

definition.value: A clinical recommendation to avoid or refrain from unnecessary chemical exposure.
The use of ultrasound to produce images of structures in the human body.

2D ultrasounds produce a flat image of the organs. 3D images show three-dimensional external images of organs or fetus. 4D ultrasounds generates an image that is continuously updated, like amoving image.

A procedure that uses high-energy sound waves to look at tissues and organs inside the body. The sound waves make echoes that form pictures of the tissues and organs on a computer screen (sonogram). Ultrasound may be used to help diagnose diseases, such as cancer. It may also be used during pregnancy to check the fetus (unborn baby) and during medical procedures, such as biopsies. Also called ultrasonography.
A procedure to measure pancreatic secretion to discriminate between pancreatic and nonpancreatic causes of malabsorption.
The quantitative measurement of digestive system tests to diagnose or treat a digestive disorder using clinical laboratory procedures, imaging tests, endoscopic or other procedures.

value.value: The act of receiving professional guidance in resolving personal conflicts and emotional problems.
Counseling designed to guide and support an individual to overcome alcohol dependence.

The process whereby an expert in hereditary disorders provides information about risk and clinical burden of a disorder or disorders to patients or relatives in families with genetic disorders as an aid to making informed and responsible decisions about marriage, children, early diagnosis, and handling disability.

definition.value: A wide range of techniques and psychotherapies aimed at controlling a person's level of stress.

value.value: A process by which a health professional provides education, recommendations, or interventions to help clients stop using tobacco products. (ACC)
The practice of piercing specific points on the body with very thin sterile needles in order to relieve pain or induce regional anesthesia.
Continuous and profound contemplation or musing on a subject or series of subjects of a deep or abstruse nature; contemplation of spiritual matters

An ancient system of practices used to balance the mind and body through exercise, meditation (focusing thoughts), and control of breathing and emotions. Yoga is being studied as a way to relieve stress and treat sleep problems.

An alternative medical system that focuses on the relationship between bodily structure (primarily that of the spine) and function, and how that relationship affects the preservation and restoration of health. Chiropractors use manipulative therapy as an integral treatment tool.
A therapeutic method of manipulation, methodical pressure, friction, and kneading of the body. (from Taber's)
Any alteration or treatment in an individual's diet with a planned goal, usually designed to improve the individual's overall health.
The restriction of energy (calorie) intake below the amount required for weight maintenance.
Delivery of enteral nutrition via a tube placed into the stomach, duodenum, or jejunum.
